        <div type="translation">
            <ab>P. L. Bat. 25 19 (English)

                    Apollonius and [. . .]tarchus to Hermias (?) greeting. You write us about the fact that you are punished (?) - - -. Try therefore to have courage in order that you may not be troubled again. Stratonicus has written us about the fact that you (or: about the oil) - - - because there is none. We have sent grapes. Do not hesitate to write us - - give in pledge the - - -. Goodbye.</ab>
